The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, November 15, 2004

 Roads to avoid

 Traffic diversion likely in Esplanade, on Red Road and Prince Anwar Shah Road for Id congregations.

 Theatre

 The Respectful Prostitute, a play by Jean-Paul Sartre, will be presented by Theatrician at Gyan Manch, 7 pm.

 Nishad, directed by Bikas Bhattacharya, will be staged by Samskar Bharati at Swabhumi, 6 pm.

 Science

 Exploring the Solar System, a science exhibition organised by British Council, at Birla Industrial amp; Technological Museum, 10 am. 

 Art watch

 The gauche and watercolor show, featuring artworks by Ganesh Haloi, Suvaprasanna, Lalu Prasad Shaw and others, at ITC Sonar Bangla.

 A group exhibition of paintings and sculpture at Chemould Art Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.

 Watercolours by Jiaur Rahman on display at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3 pm to 8 pm.

 Brando

 Marlon Brando retrospective at Nandan II and III, between 9.15 am and 11.30 am.




